<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Epistemos — Mac App Store entitlements (MAS-first sprint, 2026-05-03)
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Per `docs/fusion/MAS_FIRST_FOCUS_DOCTRINE_2026_05_03.md`. Active
  surface only — Pro-tier capabilities live in
  `Epistemos/Epistemos-Pro.entitlements` (deferred).

  TEMP-FREE-TIER NOTE (2026-05-03):
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  The `com.apple.security.application-groups` entitlement has been
  TEMPORARILY REMOVED from this file because the user's current
  signing certificate is a free Personal Team (no paid Apple Developer
  Program membership yet). Free Personal Teams cannot generate
  provisioning profiles for App Groups.

  WHAT GOT REMOVED (restore when paid Apple Developer Team is added):

      <key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
      <array>
          <string>group.com.epistemos.shared</string>
      </array>

  IMPACT WHILE REMOVED:
   - Main app and bundled XPC services CANNOT share a filesystem
     container via App Groups
   - DATA PATH BETWEEN PROCESSES MUST BE XPC MESSAGES, not shared
     `/Library/Group Containers/group.com.epistemos.shared/` files
   - Vault stays in the main app's container; XPC services receive
     data via XPC messages instead of reading from the shared group
   - This is actually a more secure architecture (XPC boundary = sole
     data path); the App Group restoration is purely operational

  RESTORATION (when paid Developer Team is available):
   1. Sign in to Apple Developer Program at developer.apple.com ($99/yr)
   2. In Apple Developer portal: register the App Group identifier
      `group.com.epistemos.shared`
   3. Update Xcode signing & capabilities to use the paid Team
   4. Restore the `application-groups` block above
   5. Remove this TEMP-FREE-TIER comment block
   6. Update `docs/fusion/MAS_FIRST_FOCUS_DOCTRINE_2026_05_03.md` §7
      to note App Groups are restored
   7. Verify XPC services that NEEDED shared container now work
      (re-enable any code paths that were XPC-message-only fallbacks)

  See also:
   - `docs/fusion/MAS_FIRST_FOCUS_DOCTRINE_2026_05_03.md` §7
   - memory: project_mas_first_focus_2026_05_03 (TEMP-FREE-TIER section)
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
	<true/>
	<!-- TEMP-FREE-TIER 2026-05-03: application-groups removed; see
	     header comment block for full restoration instructions. -->
	<key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.files.bookmarks.app-scope</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
	<true/>
</dict>
</plist>
